- 'Total accesses' is the count of access events for each service;
- 'Feedback counts' is the number of times a service has received feedback;
- 'Average ratings' is the average user rating for each service.

sql:
SELECT AVG(s.user_rating) AS average_user_rating
FROM services s
JOIN service_feedback sf ON s.service_id = sf.service_id;

SELECT AVG(s.user_rating) AS average_rating, COUNT(DISTINCT f.service_id) AS total_feedback_services
FROM services s
LEFT JOIN service_feedback f ON s.service_id = f.service_id;

